        "subject": "LU-2264 test: Create memory load for testing",
        "message": "LU-2264 test: Create memory load for testing\n\nIt can be useful to add extra memory pressure for testing.\nClient nodes are likely to use extra resources.\n\nrewrite memhog.c to include an automatic mode.  ./memhog -a will\nconsume all but 160-128mb of Ram and Swap.  The mode consumes\nthen exits at this time.  Original behavior is maintained with\nthe exception of moving the chunk size to 32mb (down from 128m)\n\nThis submission is to get this code out for basic review. The\nquestion of how to intergarete this so it is used is still\noutstanding.\n\nmemhog is quite verbose.  I am wondering about changing\nit be be more quite by default and add a -v ops flag.\n\nSigned-off-by: Keith Mannthey <keith.mannthey@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I2e52a841ed4f54985c7ec2536d49da5f44c85c57\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
